It is important the documentation is typographically
correct. This entails using typographical Unicode
characters rather than ASCII.


Emdash:
	X11: <compose> - - -
	Texinfo: ---

Endash:
	X11: <compose> - - .
	(Texinfo: --)

Hyphen:
	Not surrounded by whitespace
	Any keyboard: -

Minus:
	X11: Keypad − assuming with Unicode math operatrs

Ellipsis:
	X11: <compose> . .
	Do not use ... in Texinfo, use the UCS gryph.

Single quotes:
	‘
	  X11: <alt-gr><shift>v
	  X11: <compose> < '
	  Texinfo: `
	’
	  X11: <alt-gr><shift>b
	  X11: <compose> > '
	  Texinfo: '

Double quotes:
	“
	  X11: <alt-gr>v
	  X11: <compose> < "
	  Texinfo: ``
	”
	  X11: <alt-gr>b
	  X11: <compose> > "
	  Texinfo: ''



Glyphs used in source code:

Shy hyphen:
	X11: <compose> - - <space>
	Texinfo: @-
	Printed with red in Emacs

No breaking space: (by be used in source code)
	X11: <alt-gr><shift><space>
	Printed with magenta in Emacs

